online access with authorization2star  aIn diesem Band werden die interreligiösen Konflikte des 4. und 5. Jh. ausgehend von der Replik Contra Iulianum des Patriarchen von Alexandria, Kyrill auf die antichristliche Schrift Contra Galilaeos des letzten heidnischen Kaisers Julian in den Blick genommen. Ein Schwerpunkt liegt auf der Verortung beider Werke in ihrem zeitgenössischen Kontext, aber auch ihr ‚Nachleben‘ wird in Beiträgen zur Überlieferung und Rezeption beleuchtet.  aThis volume examines the inter-religious conflicts of the 4th and 5th centuries starting with Contra Iulianum, the reply by Patriarch Cyril of Alexandria to the anti-Christian screed Contra Galilaeos written by Rome’s last pagan emperor Julian. One focus is to situate these two works in their contemporary contexts, but chapters on their transmission and reception also explore their “afterlife.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aChristianity and culturezRome. 0aChristianity and other religionsxRoman. 0aChristianityxControversial literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aChurch historyy4th century. 0aChurch historyy5th century. 4aKaiser Julian. 4aKyrill, Patriarch von Alexandria. 4aantichristliche Schriften. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aEmperor Julian.  aPatriarch of Alexandria.  aanti-Christian writings.1 aBoulnois, Marie-Odile, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrüggemann, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Vita, Maria Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuida, Augusto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuber-Rebenich, Gerlinde, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaufhold, Hubert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary